  "text": "Associations between socioeconomic and built environments and perinatal outcomes and child health Most studies on perinatal health found interactive associations (Table 6 ). Only one study showed that a high neighbourhood income was independently positively associated with birth weight and negatively with small for gestational age [CITATION_1] . A further study on child accidents and injuries did not find an association either of neighbourhood unemployment nor the built environment [CITATION_2] .",
